# rules derived from observations and the fact that boxes are incorrectly labeled
# e.g. L1Y ^ O1W -> C1W v C1B
# In CNF:
# 1. Implication elimination: ¬(L1Y ^ O1W) v (C1W v C1B)
# 2. Push negations inward: (¬L1Y v ¬O1W) v (C1W v C1B)
(or (not L1Y) (not O1W) C1W C1B)
(or (not L2Y) (not O2W) C2W C2B)
(or (not L3Y) (not O3W) C3W C3B)
(or (not L1W) (not O1Y) C1Y C1B)
(or (not L2W) (not O2Y) C2Y C2B)
(or (not L3W) (not O3Y) C3Y C3B)

